Volcano Plot

library(EnhancedVolcano)
# Creating Function
volcano <- function(x, y){
  EnhancedVolcano(x, lab=rownames(x), x="log2FoldChange", y="pvalue",
                  title= y,
                  pCutoff=10e-3,
                  FCcutoff=1,
                  selectLab=NA,
                  cutoffLineType="twodash",
                  cutoffLineWidt=0.8,
                  pointSize=2.0,
                  colAlpha=1,
                  legendLabels=c("Not sig.", "Log (base2) FC", "p-value", "p-value & Log (base2) FC"),
                  legendLabSize=12,
                  legendPosition = "bottom",
                  legendIconSize=5.0) + coord_flip()
}

Up and Downregulated Genes

Creating a Binary Table

myList <- list(WTvsM, WTvsMe, WTvsMplusMe, WTvsMtc, WTvsMtcplusMe)
BinaryTable <- matrix(0, ncol= length(myList), nrow= length(DESeqCounts))
for (i in 1:length(myList)){
  FileExamine <- myList[[i]]
  UP <- which(FileExamine$log2FoldChange >= 1 & FileExamine$padj < 0.01)
  DOWN <- which(FileExamine$log2FoldChange <= (-1) & FileExamine$padj < 0.01)
  
  BinaryTable[UP, i] <- 1
  BinaryTable[DOWN, i] <- (-1)
}

row.names(BinaryTable) <- row.names(DESeqCounts)
colnames(BinaryTable) <- c("WTvsM", "WTvsMe", "WTvsM+Me", "WTvsMtc", "WTvsMtc+Me")
BinaryTable<-as.data.frame(BinaryTable)

#UP

MplusMeup<-which(BinaryTable[,3]==1,)
Mtcup<-which(BinaryTable[,4]==1,)
MtcplusMeup<-which(BinaryTable[,5]==1,)
MplusMeNOup<-which(BinaryTable[,3]==1&apply(BinaryTable[,c(1,2,4,5)],1,max)==0)


#DOWN
Mdown<-which(BinaryTable[,1]==(-1),)
Medown<-which(BinaryTable[,2]==(-1),)
MplusMedown<-which(BinaryTable[,3]==(-1),)

Heatmaps

library(ComplexHeatmap)
library(circlize)

Creating Function

# Creating Function
heat <- function(x, y, z){
  # subsetting tables
  a <- BinaryTable[x,]
  b <- BinaryTable[y,]
  c <- rbind(a, b)
  d <- z[rownames(c),]

  filter <- d[which(abs(d$log2FoldChange)>1 & d$padj<0.01),]
  filter <-as.data.frame(filter)
  # selecting top 20 genes only applies to conditions where it has >=20 regulated genes
  filter <-filter[order(filter$padj),][1:20,]
  mat<- counts(DESeqCounts, normalized=T)[rownames(filter),]

  #getting log2FC value and basemean value
  log2_val<-as.matrix(filter$log2FoldChange)
  colnames(log2_val)<-"log2FC"

  mean<- as.matrix(filter$baseMean)
  colnames(mean)<-"AveExpr"

  #maps values between b/w/r for min and max log2 values
  col_log2FC<-colorRamp2(c(min(log2_val), 0, max(log2_val)), c("blue", "white", "red"))
  col_AveExpr<-colorRamp2(c(quantile(mean)[1], quantile(mean)[4]), c("white", "red"))

  #calculate z-score
  mat.z<-t(apply(mat, 1, scale))
  colnames(mat.z) <- colnames(Median_counts)

  #Heatmap
  ha <- HeatmapAnnotation(summary=anno_summary(gp=gpar(fill=2),
                                             height=unit(2, "cm")))
  h1 <- Heatmap(mat.z, cluster_rows=F, cluster_columns=T, column_labels=colnames(mat.z),
              name="Z-score", column_title="mSSSI+MeCP2 (non-overlaps)",
              column_title_gp = gpar(fontsize = 18, fontface = "bold"),
              column_names_gp = grid::gpar(fontsize = 14))
  h2 <- Heatmap(log2_val, row_labels=rownames(filter), cluster_rows=F,
              name="log2FC", top_annotation=ha, col=col_log2FC,
              cell_fun=function(j,i,x,y,w,h,col){
                grid.text(round(log2_val[i,j],2), x, y)
              })
  h3 <- Heatmap(mean, row_labels=rownames(filter), cluster_rows=F,
              row_names_gp = grid::gpar(fontsize = 14),
              name="Ave Expr", col=col_AveExpr)
  h<-h1+h2+h3 
  h
}

Creating Function

RunGo <- function(genes_to_test, Bgenes){
  GO_result <- enrichGO(gene = genes_to_test,
                        universe = Bgenes,
                        OrgDb = org.EcK12.eg.db,
                        ont = 'ALL',
                        keyType = 'SYMBOL',
                        pAdjustMethod = 'BH',
                        pvalueCutoff = 0.05,
                        qvalueCutoff = 0.05)
  as.data.frame(GO_result)
  dotplot(GO_result, split="ONTOLOGY") + facet_grid(ONTOLOGY~., scale="free") 
}

CG stretches

Functions

Identifying high CG stretch

CGstretch <- function(x, y){
  for(i in 1:length(x)){
    seq <- x[[i]]
    a <- 1
    
    Nstretch <- 0
    while(a+100<length(seq)){
      TempSeq <- seq[a:(a+100)]
      M <- count(TempSeq, 2)
      CGs <- M["cg"]
      if(CGs>y){Nstretch<-Nstretch+1}
      a<-a+5
    }
    NStretch<-Nstretch/length(seq)
    
    AllCGStretch<-c(AllCGStretch, NStretch)
  }
  return(AllCGStretch)
}

Histogram

histogram <- function(x, y){
  h = hist(x$AllCGStretch)
  h$density = h$counts / sum(h$counts) * 100
  plot(h, freq=FALSE, main=paste(y, "CG Stretch Density"),
       xlab="High CG stretch proportion")
}

Subset

subset <- function(x, y, DinucsProps){
  x <- as.data.frame(AllCGStretch)
  
  rownames(x) <- rownames(DinucsProps[y,])
  
  return(x)
}

# Boxplot and Wilcox Test function
bxplot <- function(x, y, z, number){
  boxplot(x$AllCGStretch, y$AllCGStretch, z$AllCGStretch,
          outline=F, notch=T,
          ylab= paste(number, "CG Stretch Proportion"), xlab="Condition",
          main= paste(number, "CG Stretch Proportion"), cex.axis=1.4, cex.main=1.8, yaxt="n", cex.lab=1.4,
          names=c("non-DEGs", "mSSSI+MeCP2 (NO)\nupregulated genes", "mSSSI+MeCP2 (NO)\ndownregulated genes"),
          col = c("brown1", "cadetblue2", "cadetblue2"), border="black",
          las=1, cex.axis=0.75)
  axis(2, cex.axis=1.8, mgp=c(3,1,0))
  abline(h=median(x$AllCGStretch), lwd=2, col="red", lty=2)
}

#wilcoxon test
wilcox <- function(x, y){
  wilcox.test(x$AllCGStretch, y$AllCGStretch, paired=F, conf.int=0.95)
}

Boxplots and Wilcoxon Test

bxplot(nonDEGs8, MplusMeNOup8, MplusMeNOdown8, 8)
bxplot(nonDEGs10, MplusMeNOup10, MplusMeNOdown10, 10)
bxplot(nonDEGs12, MplusMeNOup12, MplusMeNOdown12, 12)
bxplot(nonDEGs15, MplusMeNOup15, MplusMeNOdown15, 15)
bxplot(nonDEGs17, MplusMeNOup17, MplusMeNOdown17, 17)

# Upregulated
a <- wilcox(MplusMeNOup8, nonDEGs8)
b <- wilcox(MplusMeNOup10, nonDEGs10)
c <- wilcox(MplusMeNOup12, nonDEGs12)

# Downregulated
d <- wilcox(MplusMeNOdown8, nonDEGs8)
e <- wilcox(MplusMeNOdown10, nonDEGs10)
f <- wilcox(MplusMeNOdown12, nonDEGs12)

MyPs_CGstretch <- c(a$p.value, b$p.value, c$p.value, d$p.value, e$p.value, f$p.value)
MyPadjs_CGstretch <- p.adjust(MyPs_CGstretch, method="bonferroni")
